<subSubSection pageId="26" pageNumber="27" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="26.[151,1436,572,1499]" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,266,572,598]" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">Diagnosis</emphasis>
(after 
<bibRefCitation author="Kirejtshuk, A. G. &amp; Kovalev, A. V." box="[354,691,572,599]" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" pagination="226 - 242" refId="ref106508" refString="Kirejtshuk, A. G. &amp; Kovalev, A. V. (2016) A new genus of the subfamily Cillaeinae (Coleoptera, Nitidulidae) from the Philippines and New Guinea with notes on the taxonomy and phylogeny of the subfamily. Zootaxa, 4205 (3), 226 - 242. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4205.3.3" type="journal article" year="2016">Kirejtshuk &amp; Kovalev 2016</bibRefCitation>
). This genus is distinct from other genera from 
<collectingCountry box="[1279,1382,572,598]" name="Australia" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">Australia</collectingCountry>
and surrounding territories in its peculiar set of characters including the head with eyes dislodged to anterior part of head and behind eye moderately narrowed; antennal grooves well expressed and distinctly outlined; pronotum with posterior angles having a distinct tip; tergites uncovered by elytra with elongate paramedian depressions; abdominal laterosternites V and VI subparallel-sided or narrowed posteriorly; distance between metacoxae narrowly separated or subcontiguous; elytra with diffuse punctures; median part of prosternum more less convex and prosternal process forming a unified median plate; body integument with scarcely conspicuous hairs or almost without them; distance between mesocoxae subequal with or smaller than that between procoxae; procoxae moderately separated; apex of female pygidium distinctly serrate; antennomeres 2 and 3 comparable in length.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="26.[151,1436,572,1499]" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">
This genus is distinct among cillaeines by its comparatively small eyes and rather long temples, which can be compared with those only in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Murray" authorityYear="1864" box="[489,610,932,958]" class="Insecta" family="Nitidulidae" genus="Ithyphenes" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[489,610,932,958]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">Ithyphenes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(see below). It is externally similar to the genus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Modiglianii Grouvelle" authorityYear="1897" box="[1181,1274,932,958]" class="Insecta" family="Nitidulidae" genus="Cillaeus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1181,1274,932,958]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">Cillaeus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Modiglianii Grouvelle" authorityYear="1897" box="[1334,1427,932,958]" class="Insecta" family="Nitidulidae" genus="Cillaeus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1334,1427,932,958]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">Cillaeus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
- like genera and subgenera (
<taxonomicName authorityName="Grouvelle" authorityYear="1898" box="[464,618,968,994]" class="Insecta" family="Nitidulidae" genus="Carpophilops" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[464,618,968,994]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">Carpophilops</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName box="[633,789,968,994]" class="Insecta" family="Nitidulidae" genus="Cillaeopeplus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[633,789,968,994]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">Cillaeopeplus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Murray" authorityYear="1864" box="[803,959,968,994]" class="Insecta" family="Nitidulidae" genus="Halepopeplus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[803,959,968,994]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">Halepopeplus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Murray" authorityYear="1864" box="[974,1122,968,994]" class="Insecta" family="Nitidulidae" genus="Liparopeplus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[974,1122,968,994]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">Liparopeplus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Kirejtshuk &amp; Kovalev" authorityYear="2022" box="[1138,1314,968,994]" class="Insecta" family="Nitidulidae" genus="Paracillaeopsis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" status="stat. nov.">
<emphasis box="[1138,1314,968,994]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">Paracillaeopsis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1322,1429,968,994]" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1322,1429,968,994]" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">stat. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Kirejtshuk" authorityYear="2001" box="[151,292,1004,1030]" class="Insecta" family="Nitidulidae" genus="Tokocillaeus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[151,292,1004,1030]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">Tokocillaeus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Fairmaire" authorityYear="1880" box="[304,458,1004,1030]" class="Insecta" family="Nitidulidae" genus="Xanthopeplus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[304,458,1004,1030]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">Xanthopeplus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) by its elongate subparallel-sided and not strongly convex body, (sub)quadrate pronotum (although some members of the aforementioned groups demonstrate rather arcuate pronotal sides), simple labrum at most with a clear median suture (usually only line remains), at least three abdominal segments uncovered by elytra, three preapical abdominal and slightly convex underside.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="26.[151,1436,572,1499]" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">
See also the above key to the cillaeine genera of 
<collectingCountry box="[698,801,1148,1174]" name="Australia" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">Australia</collectingCountry>
and surrounding territories and the detailed diagnosis of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Kirejtshuk et Kovalev" authorityYear="2016" box="[151,291,1184,1210]" class="Insecta" family="Nitidulidae" genus="Allenipeplus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[151,291,1184,1210]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">Allenipeplus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in 
<bibRefCitation author="Kirejtshuk, A. G. &amp; Kovalev, A. V." box="[327,717,1184,1210]" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" pagination="226 - 242" refId="ref106508" refString="Kirejtshuk, A. G. &amp; Kovalev, A. V. (2016) A new genus of the subfamily Cillaeinae (Coleoptera, Nitidulidae) from the Philippines and New Guinea with notes on the taxonomy and phylogeny of the subfamily. Zootaxa, 4205 (3), 226 - 242. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4205.3.3" type="journal article" year="2016">Kirejtshuk &amp; Kovalev (2016: 228)</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="26.[151,1436,572,1499]" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,351,1220,1246]" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">Composition</emphasis>
. This genus consists of four described species (
<bibRefCitation author="Kirejtshuk, A. G. &amp; Kovalev, A. V." box="[884,1201,1220,1247]" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" pagination="226 - 242" refId="ref106508" refString="Kirejtshuk, A. G. &amp; Kovalev, A. V. (2016) A new genus of the subfamily Cillaeinae (Coleoptera, Nitidulidae) from the Philippines and New Guinea with notes on the taxonomy and phylogeny of the subfamily. Zootaxa, 4205 (3), 226 - 242. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4205.3.3" type="journal article" year="2016">Kirejtshuk &amp; Kovalev 2016</bibRefCitation>
) represented only by females (
<taxonomicName authorityName="Kirejtshuk et Kovalev" authorityYear="2016" box="[253,555,1256,1282]" class="Insecta" family="Nitidulidae" genus="Allenipeplus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="philippinensis">
<emphasis box="[253,555,1256,1282]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">Allenipeplus philippinensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from 
<collectingCountry box="[619,748,1256,1282]" name="Philippines" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">Philippines</collectingCountry>
, Luzon, 
<taxonomicName authority="Kirejtshuk et Kovalev, 2016" authorityName="Kirejtshuk" authorityYear="2016" box="[841,1239,1256,1283]" class="Insecta" family="Nitidulidae" genus="Allenipeplus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="alius">
<emphasis box="[841,924,1256,1282]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">A. alius</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Kirejtshuk, A. G. &amp; Kovalev, A. V." box="[929,1239,1256,1283]" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" pagination="226 - 242" refId="ref106508" refString="Kirejtshuk, A. G. &amp; Kovalev, A. V. (2016) A new genus of the subfamily Cillaeinae (Coleoptera, Nitidulidae) from the Philippines and New Guinea with notes on the taxonomy and phylogeny of the subfamily. Zootaxa, 4205 (3), 226 - 242. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4205.3.3" type="journal article" year="2016">Kirejtshuk et Kovalev, 2016</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
from 
<collectingCountry box="[1303,1432,1256,1282]" name="Philippines" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">Philippines</collectingCountry>
, Mindoro, 
<taxonomicName authority="Kirejtshuk et Kovalev, 2016" authorityName="Kirejtshuk" authorityYear="2016" box="[265,760,1292,1319]" class="Insecta" family="Nitidulidae" genus="Allenipeplus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="harmonicus">
<emphasis box="[265,430,1292,1318]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">A. harmonicus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Kirejtshuk, A. G. &amp; Kovalev, A. V." box="[439,760,1292,1319]" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" pagination="226 - 242" refId="ref106508" refString="Kirejtshuk, A. G. &amp; Kovalev, A. V. (2016) A new genus of the subfamily Cillaeinae (Coleoptera, Nitidulidae) from the Philippines and New Guinea with notes on the taxonomy and phylogeny of the subfamily. Zootaxa, 4205 (3), 226 - 242. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4205.3.3" type="journal article" year="2016">Kirejtshuk et Kovalev, 2016</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
from 
<collectingCountry box="[832,961,1292,1318]" name="Philippines" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">Philippines</collectingCountry>
, Mindanao and 
<taxonomicName authority="Kirejtshuk et Kovalev, 2016" authorityName="Kirejtshuk et Kovalev" authorityYear="2016" class="Insecta" family="Nitidulidae" genus="Allenipeplus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="vitellinus">
<emphasis box="[1145,1281,1292,1318]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">A. vitellinus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Kirejtshuk, A. G. &amp; Kovalev, A. V." pageId="26" pageNumber="27" pagination="226 - 242" refId="ref106508" refString="Kirejtshuk, A. G. &amp; Kovalev, A. V. (2016) A new genus of the subfamily Cillaeinae (Coleoptera, Nitidulidae) from the Philippines and New Guinea with notes on the taxonomy and phylogeny of the subfamily. Zootaxa, 4205 (3), 226 - 242. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4205.3.3" type="journal article" year="2016">Kirejtshuk et Kovalev, 2016</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
from 
<collectingCountry box="[387,611,1328,1355]" name="Papua New Guinea" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">Papua New Guinea</collectingCountry>
). Also, two undescribed species from 
<collectingRegion box="[1043,1183,1328,1355]" country="Papua New Guinea" name="New Ireland" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">New Ireland</collectingRegion>
and Malayan Fraser’s Hill are available, and there is a single male specimen from the latter locality which is characterized by the anal sclerite slightly exposed from under the pygidial apex and withour clear serration along its subtruncate apex.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="26" pageNumber="27" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="26.[151,1436,572,1499]" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,345,1436,1462]" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">Distribution</emphasis>
. This genus is known after four described species from 
<collectingCountry box="[1008,1134,1436,1462]" name="Philippines" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">Philippines</collectingCountry>
and New Gunea and two species from the Indo-Malayan Region remain undescribed (see above).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
